               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                       <support>Wax tablets; Tablet I: H. 13,5-14,1 x W. 17,7 x Th. c. 0,35 cm, Tablet II: H. 14,1x W. 17,7 x Th. c. 0,35 cm</support>
                       <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Tablet II consists of two halves  with different inv. nrs. The wax coating of side I A is rather damaged and only a few traces of writing are visible. On I B,  a rectangle of c. 10,5 x 12,8 cm with a panel, and unidentified signs .The inner side of tablet II A is well preserved. On side II B the wax is damaged and shows no more than traces of some letters. On both tablets, one of the long sides is missing.</ab>
                       </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                          <ab type="lines">Only a few traces of writing are visible on side I A. 2 lines of unidentified characters on side I B; below some traces, upside down. 15 lines on side II A. On side II B the wax is damaged and shows no more than traces of some letters.</ab>
                        </layout>
